{"id":169,"ayahs":[{"number":150,"arabic":"وَلَمَّا رَجَعَ مُوسَىٰٓ إِلَىٰ قَوْمِهِۦ غَضْبَٰنَ أَسِفًۭا قَالَ بِئْسَمَا خَلَفْتُمُونِى مِنۢ بَعْدِىٓ ۖ أَعَجِلْتُمْ أَمْرَ رَبِّكُمْ ۖ وَأَلْقَى ٱلْأَلْوَاحَ وَأَخَذَ بِرَأْسِ أَخِيهِ يَجُرُّهُۥٓ إِلَيْهِ ۚ قَالَ ٱبْنَ أُمَّ إِنَّ ٱلْقَوْمَ ٱسْتَضْعَفُونِى وَكَادُوا۟ يَقْتُلُونَنِى فَلَا تُشْمِتْ بِىَ ٱلْأَعْدَآءَ وَلَا تَجْعَلْنِى مَعَ ٱلْقَوْمِ ٱلظَّٰلِمِينَ","translation":"And when Moses returned to his people, full of wrath and sorrow, he exclaimed: \"Vile is the course which you have followed in my absence! Have you forsaken your Sustainer's commandment?\" And he threw down the tablets [of the Law], and seized his brother's head, dragging him towards himself. Cried Aaron: \"O my mother's son! Behold, the people brought me low and almost slew me: so let not mine enemies rejoice at my affliction, and count me not among the evildoing folk!\"","audio":"https://cdn.islamic.network/quran/audio/128/ar.alafasy/1104.mp3","surahId":7,"words":[{"id":80464,"position":1,"arabic":"وَلَمَّا","translation":"এবং যখন","audioUrl":"wbw/007_150_001.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":80465,"position":2,"arabic":"رَجَعَ","translation":"প্রত্যাবর্তন করলো","audioUrl":"wbw/007_150_002.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":80466,"position":3,"arabic":"مُوسَىٰٓ","translation":"মূসা","audioUrl":"wbw/007_150_003.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":80467,"position":4,"arabic":"إِلَىٰ","translation":"নিকট","audioUrl":"wbw/007_150_004.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":80468,"position":5,"arabic":"قَوْمِهِۦ","translation":"তার জাতির","audioUrl":"wbw/007_150_005.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":80469,"position":6,"arabic":"غَضْبَـٰنَ","translation":"রাগান্বিত হয়ে","audioUrl":"wbw/007_150_006.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":80470,"position":7,"arabic":"أَسِفًۭا","translation":"দুঃখিত অবস্হায়","audioUrl":"wbw/007_150_007.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":80471,"position":8,"arabic":"قَالَ","translation":"সে বললো","audioUrl":"wbw/007_150_008.mp3","cha